### CORS issue

If you are using the demo, you might encounter a CORS issue. This is because the Keystone.js backend is hosted on a different domain than the Next.js frontend. To fix this, you can install the [Moesif Origin & CORS Changer](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/moesif-origin-cors-change/digfbfaphojjndkpccljibejjbppifbc) Chrome extension and change the origin to `https://nextjs-ecommerce.repository.host`.

### Backend

The backend is deployed right now on the Heroku free tier. Live demo: [https://shareed-backend.herokuapp.com/](https://shareed-backend.herokuapp.com/signin).

Demo credentials:

```sh
email: testmail@gmail.com
password: password1
```

The Heroku backend is connected to a PostgreSQL database on [ElephantSQL](https://www.elephantsql.com/).

The password reset uses a sandboxed Mailgun account and only works with one email: dzwjxgqv@sharklasers.com

To read the password reset email, go to [https://www.guerrillamail.com/](https://www.guerrillamail.com/) and set the inbox to "dzwjxgqv@sharklasers.com".
